  "market_context": "On Sep 25, 2023, NQ closed inside a 15-minute candle, indicating anticipation of a move down into an internal fair value gap (discount zone). The analyst identified an external liquidity draw at a prior swing high and awaited a stop raid in the opposite direction before entering short on the 30-second chart.",
  "key_observation": "Price closed inside a 15-minute range, signaling a likely move toward internal range liquidity (a 15-min FVG below), with a subsequent 5-min sweep of a swing high confirming the bearish stop raid.",
  "analysis_steps": [
    "Step 1: On the 15-minute chart, the analyst observed price closing inside a candle, anticipating a move down to an internal fair value gap (IRL) — specifically a 15-min FVG between 14890.0 and 14905.0.",
    "Step 2: Dropped to the 5-minute chart to locate a stop raid in the opposite direction (bullish sweep); identified a sweep of a prior swing high followed by a down-close candle confirming the raid.",
    "Step 3: Dropped to the 30-second chart and waited for a fair value gap forming after the down-close candle; entered short at the 30-sec FVG with a 10–12 point stop.",
    "Step 4: Targeted a fixed 1:1 initially, but later noted higher-probability structural targets (e.g., prior 5-min low) could yield ≥2R."
  ],
  "outcome": "The entry at the 30-second FVG worked; price moved down to hit the 1:1 target and beyond toward structural lows (e.g., 14876–14890 zone), achieving at least 1.83R–2R depending on target choice.",
  "lessons": "Cameron’s model requires strict sequence: draw on liquidity → opposite-direction stop raid → lower-time-frame FVG entry. Internal liquidity (FVGs) is often targeted after external liquidity (swing highs/lows) is swept, especially when price closes inside a range.",
